        mdx_note.filter(id.gt(0))  // Assuming `id` is a valid filtering criteria
            .load(&mut conn)  // Replace get_results with load
            .await
            .map_err(|_| FlusterError::FailToFind)?;

    Ok(results)
}
Using  Instead of : The  function is the proper Diesel method to use when loading results into your struct type. Since you’re working with a collection of rows (Vec),  is more appropriate.Awaiting for the Connection:  Make sure to use the  keyword correctly when setting the connection variable, ensuring it is fully established before use.Common Type Mismatch IssuesTo further debug the type mismatch issues:: Check that your  struct aligns correctly with your database schema. Each field in the struct should match the corresponding database column in type, order, and presence. Here’s a basic example:#[derive(Queryable, Debug)]
